verse.lines:
{lang-eng}The King of love my Shepherd is,
Whose goodness faileth never;
I nothing lack if I am his
And He is mine forever.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}In death’s dark vale I fear no ill
With thee, dear Lord, beside me;
Thy rod and staff my comfort still,
Thy cross before to guide me.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Thou spread’st a table in my sight;
Thy unction, grace bestoweth:
And O what transport of delight
From Thy pure chalice floweth!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}And so through all the length of days
Thy goodness faileth never;
Good Shepherd, may I sing Thy praise
Within Thy house for ever.{/lang-eng}
